I lived next to the St Martin des Champs church. I was very touched that the church was almost burned down. I had my communion, my wedding and buried my parents. Despite no longer being part of the neighborhood. As soon as I am in the neighborhood I go to worship in this church that I love.
The church building is currently undergoing renovation. However, just at the entrance, a very small space is transformed into a mini-chapel just for gathering or lighting a candle.

The parish lights its exterior banner evening and morning with an extremely powerful spotlight; despite multiple arrests, no compassion for the family living in front of this light pollution!!! What a lack of Christian charity in this way of despising the suffering inflicted on others!
A parish with an extraordinary team in a renovated church. Not to be missed to live your faith on this side of Place de la République.
In the footsteps of Saint Martin in Paris. St. Martin's Church has many paintings with scenes from the life of St. Martin. A visit is definitely worthwhile.
